VALIDATION COHORT. When comparing the test cohort versus the validation cohort, the latter group was an older population (age 68 Æ 15 years vs. 54 Æ 17 years) with a higher incidence of hypertension (69% vs. 44%) and diabetes mellitus (30% vs. 16%) (Table 6). Echocardiographic analysis revealed similar characteristics between them, with a 42% incidence of LVH (Table 1).

