PERSPECTIVES

COMPETENCY IN MEDICAL KNOWLEDGE: When compared with Cornell voltage and other ECG criteria, the diagnosis of LVH can be enhanced by incorporating better representation of depolarization vectors in this disease.

TRANSLATIONAL OUTLOOK: Although a surrogate for more speciﬁc measurement of left ventricular mass, the electrocardiogram remains a widely available, relatively inexpensive diagnostic modality, and development of criteria that improve its diagnostic precision has implications for more efﬁcient resource utilization.

